# Sector 10: Real Estate & Construction

```
⏱  TIMELINE:       1 – 10 years
💰 STARTING COST:  ₹1L – ₹500Cr+
🐢 REVENUE SPEED:  Slow (but high returns)
DEPENDS ON:        Land, permits, capital, labor, building materials
```

---

## 10.1 Development

---

### 🔴 358. Residential Construction

**What it is:** Building residential projects — apartments, villas, row houses, gated communities. From small 10-unit projects to 1,000+ unit townships.

**Players:** DLF (big), Godrej Properties (big), Prestige (big), Sobha (big), individual local builders (lakhs).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — 3-7 years per project.

**Challenges:** 💰 ₹5Cr-5,000Cr+ investment · 📜 RERA registration, environmental clearance, municipal approvals · 🌊 Real estate cycles (2-3 year boom/bust) · 👥 Interest rate changes by RBI impact demand · ⚙ Labor management, material procurement.

**Mistake:** Over-leveraging during boom. When cycle turns, unsold inventory + interest = bankruptcy. Survivors build conservatively with pre-sales.

**One-liner:** Build homes — India's urbanization is a mega-trend, but conservative leverage and pre-sales discipline separate survivors from failures.

---

### 🔴 359. Commercial Building

**What it is:** Developing office spaces, IT parks, business centers — leasing to corporates for rental income.

**Players:** DLF (big), Embassy Group (big), Prestige (big), RMZ Corp (Indian, big), individual commercial developers.

**Model:** Rental 🔑 (lease income) + Product Sale 📦 (strata sale) | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — 2-5 years to build + lease.

**Challenges:** 💰 ₹50Cr-5,000Cr+ · 📜 Zoning, FSI, environmental approvals · 📈 Co-working/hybrid work reducing demand for traditional offices · ⚙ Must build to Grade A specifications for MNC tenants.

**Mistake:** Building generic office space. Today's corporate tenants want Green Building certified (IGBC/LEED), smart building features, and wellness amenities. Spec matters more than location alone.

**One-liner:** Build office spaces — Green Building certification and smart features are now table stakes for corporate tenants.

---

### 🔴 360. Township Development

**What it is:** Developing large integrated townships — residential + commercial + retail + schools + hospitals + parks. Mini-cities within cities.

**Players:** Lodha (big), Hiranandani (big), Prestige (big), individual township developers.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — 10-15 year horizon.

**Challenges:** 💰 ₹500Cr-10,000Cr+ · 📜 Special Township Policy approvals · ⚙ Multi-phase construction management · 🕐 10-15 year commitment · 🌊 Market cycles during such long projects.

**Mistake:** Not building infrastructure (roads, sewage, water) first. Buyers who move in before infrastructure is ready become hostile — and vocal.

**One-liner:** Build townships — infrastructure first, then residences; nothing angers buyers more than a home without water/roads.

---

### 🔴 361. Affordable Housing

**What it is:** Building homes for lower-income buyers — EWS (Economically Weaker Section) and LIG (Lower Income Group) under PMAY and similar schemes.

**Players:** Tata Housing (big), Mahindra Lifespaces (big), individual affordable housing developers.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow.

**Challenges:** 💰 Low selling price means thin margins · 📜 Government subsidy processes are slow · ⚙ Must optimize construction cost to the rupee · 📈 Land in affordable locations is hard to find · 🕐 Subsidy disbursement delays.

**Mistake:** Using the same construction methods as luxury housing. Affordable housing needs precast, modular, and technology-driven construction to hit cost targets profitably.

**One-liner:** Build affordable homes — profitability depends on construction technology that reduces cost per square foot.

---

### 🔴 362. Industrial Parks & SEZs

**What it is:** Developing dedicated zones for industries — industrial parks, Special Economic Zones, logistics parks, manufacturing hubs.

**Players:** Mahindra Industrial Park (big), Embassy Industrial Parks (big), MIDC (Maharashtra, govt), individual developers.

**Model:** Rental 🔑 (lease) + Product Sale 📦 (plot sales) | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — 5-10 years.

**Challenges:** 💰 ₹100Cr-5,000Cr+ · 📜 SEZ approvals, environmental clearance, land acquisition · ⚙ Providing power, water, road infrastructure · 👥 Land acquisition politics · 🕐 Long development timeline.

**Mistake:** Not securing anchor tenants before development. One large company committing to 30-50% of the park de-risks the entire project and attracts other tenants.

**One-liner:** Build industrial parks — secure anchor tenants first; one major company de-risks the entire project.

---

### 🔴 363. Shopping Mall Development

**What it is:** Developing retail malls — anchor stores, food courts, entertainment, fashion, lifestyle brands.

**Players:** Phoenix Mills (Indian, big), DLF (big), Lulu Group (big), Nexus (Blackstone, big).

**Model:** Rental 🔑 (lease + revenue share) | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — 3-5 years to build + stabilize occupancy.

**Challenges:** 💰 ₹100Cr-2,000Cr+ · 📈 E-commerce threatening retail foot traffic · ⚙ Tenant mix curation is an art · 📜 Municipal approvals, fire safety · 🌊 Pandemic showed malls can go empty.

**Mistake:** Not investing in experiential retail. Malls that are just shopping are dying. Malls with entertainment (cinema, gaming, trampoline parks), F&B, and events thrive.

**One-liner:** Build malls — experiential (entertainment + F&B + events) malls thrive; shopping-only malls are dying.

---

### 🔴 364. Hotel & Resort Development

**What it is:** Building hospitality properties — hotels, resorts, service apartments — and either operating or leasing to hotel chains.

**Players:** ITC Hotels (big), Indian Hotels/Taj (big), Lemon Tree (Indian, big), individual hotel developers.

**Model:** Rental 🔑 + Service Fee 🔧 (management contract) | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — 3-7 years.

**Challenges:** 💰 ₹10Cr-500Cr+ · 📜 Tourism department, fire, liquor licenses · ⚙ Design must meet brand standards if franchised · 🌊 Tourism is cyclical + pandemic risk.

**Mistake:** Building without a hotel brand tie-up. A hotel branded under Marriott/Taj gets 3-5x the room rate vs unbranded. Sign a management contract before construction.

**One-liner:** Build hotels — sign a brand management contract before construction; branded commands 3-5x unbranded rates.

---

### 🔴 365. Warehouse & Logistics Parks

**What it is:** Developing Grade A warehouses and logistics hubs — for e-commerce, 3PL, manufacturing, cold storage.

**Players:** Embassy Industrial Parks (big), IndoSpace (big), ESR India (big), individual developers.

**Model:** Rental 🔑 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium — e-commerce driving massive demand.

**Challenges:** 💰 ₹20Cr-500Cr per park · 📜 Industrial zoning, environment · 📈 E-commerce boom = warehouse boom · ⚙ Must meet Grade A specs (height, floor load, dock doors).

**Mistake:** Building low-spec warehouses. Grade A warehouses (12m+ height, 5 ton/sqm floor load, adequate dock doors) lease at 2x the rate of basic sheds.

**One-liner:** Build warehouses — Grade A specifications command premium rents; e-commerce is driving explosive demand.

---

### 🔴 366. Data Center Construction

**What it is:** Building facilities to house servers and IT infrastructure — with redundant power, cooling, security, and connectivity.

**Players:** NTT Data (big), Adani (entering, big), Yotta (Indian, big), CtrlS (Indian, big), STT GDC (big).

**Model:** Rental 🔑 (per rack/MW pricing) | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — 2-4 years to build.

**Challenges:** 💰 ₹200Cr-5,000Cr+ · ⚙ 99.99%+ uptime requirements · 🧠 Power, cooling, and fire suppression engineering · 📜 Land near fiber routes and power stations · 👥 India's digital push + data localization mandates creating demand.

**Mistake:** Under-provisioning power. Data centers live or die on power reliability. Budget for 2N redundancy (double backup for everything).

**One-liner:** Build data centers — India's data localization push creates demand; power redundancy is the #1 design priority.

---

### 🔴 367. Smart City Infrastructure

**What it is:** Building smart city components — intelligent traffic management, smart street lighting, public WiFi, smart water metering, city surveillance, digital governance platforms.

**Players:** L&T Smart World (big), Tata Communications (big), Siemens (big), individual smart city contractors.

**Model:** Contract 📋 (government) + Service Fee 🔧 (O&M) | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — government procurement.

**Challenges:** 📜 Smart City Mission tenders — bureaucratic · 💰 Large project scope · 🕐 Government payment delays · ⚙ Integrating multiple technologies · 🧠 IoT + urban planning expertise.

**Mistake:** Bidding on complete smart city projects without consortium partners. These projects need telecom + IT + civil + urban planning expertise. Form consortiums with complementary partners.

**One-liner:** Build smart city tech — form consortiums with complementary partners; no single company has all the expertise.

---

## 10.2 Real Estate Services

---

### 🟢 368. Property Brokerage

**What it is:** Connecting property buyers with sellers or tenants with landlords. Earning commission per deal.

**Players:** 99acres (platform, big), MagicBricks (big), NoBroker (Indian, big), Square Yards (Indian), individual brokers (millions).

**Model:** Commission 💰 (1-2% of sale value or 1-2 months rent) | **Revenue:** ⚡ Fast — one deal = ₹50K-10L+.

**Challenges:** 📈 NoBroker/direct platforms threatening agents · 📜 RERA registration · 🧠 Deep local market knowledge · ⚙ Deals take 1-6 months · 💰 Zero income between deals.

**Mistake:** Listing properties without verifying legal status. One disputed property deal destroys reputation forever.

**One-liner:** Connect buyers and sellers — zero investment, but legal verification and local expertise make you valuable.

---

### 🟡 369. Property Management

**What it is:** Managing properties on behalf of owners — tenant finding, rent collection, maintenance coordination, legal compliance.

**Players:** NestAway (Indian, medium), individual property managers, housing society management companies.

**Model:** Commission 💰 (8-15% of monthly rent) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** ⚙ Tenant issues (late payment, damage, disputes) · 📈 NoBroker/NestAway competing · 💰 Revenue scales only with number of properties managed · 📜 Rental law compliance.

**Mistake:** Not using technology. Property management with spreadsheets doesn't scale. Simple software for rent tracking, maintenance tickets, and tenant communication is essential.

**One-liner:** Manage properties for owners — technology (even simple) for rent tracking and maintenance is essential to scale.

---

### 🟡 370. Real Estate Appraisal

**What it is:** Professionally valuing properties — for bank loans, insurance, tax assessment, legal disputes, investment decisions.

**Players:** Individual registered valuers, CRISIL (big — institutional valuation), Knight Frank (big).

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 Registered Valuer certification (IBBI) required · 🧠 Deep understanding of property markets + regulations · 📈 Banks appointing their own panel valuers · 💰 Per-valuation fees are moderate.

**Mistake:** Inflating valuations to please clients. Regulators track valuation accuracy. Consistent overvaluation leads to panel removal and legal trouble.

**One-liner:** Value properties professionally — integrity is everything; inflated valuations destroy credibility and invite regulatory action.

---

### 🟡 371. Title Search & Verification

**What it is:** Investigating property ownership history, encumbrances, litigation, and legal status — ensuring the title is clear before purchase.

**Players:** Individual property lawyers, title insurance companies (emerging in India), search firms.

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 | **Revenue:** ⚡ Fast.

**Challenges:** 🧠 Must understand land records, registration, revenue records · 📜 Each state has different land record systems · ⚙ Records are often incomplete or contradictory · 📈 Digitization making some searches easier.

**Mistake:** Only doing online searches. Indian land records are notoriously incomplete. Physical verification at sub-registrar offices and revenue departments is still necessary.

**One-liner:** Verify property titles — always do physical verification at sub-registrar offices; online records alone are unreliable in India.

---

### 🟢 372. Home Staging & Design

**What it is:** Furnishing and decorating properties for sale or rent — making them look attractive to buyers/tenants. Also includes real estate photography.

**Players:** Individual home stagers, interior designers offering staging, real estate photography services.

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 | **Revenue:** ⚡ Fast.

**Challenges:** 📈 Concept is new in India — market education needed · 💰 Furniture inventory investment · ⚙ Must turn around quickly (2-3 days) · 🧠 Design sense + understanding buyer psychology.

**Mistake:** Over-staging with personal taste. Staging should be neutral and aspirational — buyers need to imagine THEMSELVES living there, not admire YOUR style.

**One-liner:** Stage homes for sale — neutral, aspirational styling helps homes sell faster and for more; new concept with first-mover potential in India.

---

### 🟡 373. Rental Management (Airbnb)

**What it is:** Managing short-term rental properties for owners — listing on Airbnb/Booking.com, guest communication, cleaning, pricing optimization.

**Players:** SaffronStays (Indian, managed stays), individual Airbnb managers, Vista Rooms (Indian, premium).

**Model:** Commission 💰 (15-25% of booking revenue) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** ⚙ Guest management 24/7 · 🌊 Seasonal demand · 💰 Cleaning and maintenance costs · 📜 Local regulations on short-term rentals · 📈 Platform dependency.

**Mistake:** Managing too many properties without systems. 5 well-managed properties with 5-star reviews earn more than 20 poorly managed ones with complaints.

**One-liner:** Manage Airbnb properties — quality over quantity; 5-star reviews on fewer properties beat bad reviews on many.

---

### 🟢 374. Real Estate Photography

**What it is:** Professional photography and videography for property listings — drones, wide-angle, virtual tours, 3D walkthroughs.

**Players:** Individual real estate photographers, Matterport (3D tours, big), property listing platforms.

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 | **Revenue:** ⚡ Fast.

**Challenges:** 📈 Agents using phone cameras · 💰 Drone and camera equipment ₹1L-5L · 🧠 Wide-angle and lighting techniques specific to interiors · ⚙ Must deliver fast (same-day editing).

**Mistake:** Not offering video and drone. Still photos alone are becoming commodity. Video walkthroughs + drone aerials + 3D tours command 3-5x premium.

**One-liner:** Photograph properties — video walkthroughs and drone shots command premium over just still photos.

---

### 🟡 375. Co-Working Space Operator

**What it is:** Operating shared office spaces — hot desks, dedicated desks, private cabins, meeting rooms for freelancers, startups, and remote workers.

**Players:** WeWork India (big), 91springboard (Indian, big), Awfis (Indian, big), individual co-working operators.

**Model:** Subscription 🔄 (monthly membership) + Rental 🔑 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 💰 Fit-out cost ₹50L-5Cr · 📈 Post-COVID hybrid work creating demand AND reducing need · ⚙ Occupancy management — must stay above 70% to be profitable · 💰 Long lease commitments with landlords.

**Mistake:** Over-investing in fancy interiors. Members care about internet speed, comfortable chairs, meeting room availability, and community — more than designer furniture.

**One-liner:** Run co-working spaces — fast internet, good chairs, and community matter more than Instagram-worthy interiors.

---

### 🟡 376. Co-Living Space Operator

**What it is:** Managed shared living — furnished rooms with shared kitchen, lounge, laundry for young professionals and students.

**Players:** Stanza Living (Indian, big), Zolo (Indian, big), CoHo (Indian), individual PG operators going premium.

**Model:** Subscription 🔄 (monthly rent) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 💰 Furnishing and maintaining units · ⚙ Tenant management, housekeeping · 📈 Traditional PGs compete on price · 📜 Local rental regulations.

**Mistake:** Just being a "fancy PG." Co-living must offer community (events, networking, common areas) and services (cleaning, food, WiFi). Without that, you're just expensive PG accommodation.

**One-liner:** Run co-living — community and services differentiate from PGs; without them, you're just overpriced accommodation.

---

### 🟡 377. Real Estate Consultancy

**What it is:** Advising on large real estate decisions — land acquisition strategy, project feasibility, highest-and-best-use analysis, market research for developers.

**Players:** JLL (big), CBRE (big), Knight Frank (big), Anarock (Indian, big), individual consultants.

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 🧠 Deep market knowledge + analytical skills · 📈 Big 4 real estate consultancies dominate · 💰 Project-based revenue is lumpy · ⚙ Must maintain market data and research capability.

**Mistake:** Giving advice without data. Real estate consultancy must be backed by transaction data, market surveys, and financial modeling — not just opinions.

**One-liner:** Advise on real estate deals — data-backed recommendations beat opinions; invest in market research capability.

---

## 10.3 Real Estate Investment

---

### 🟡 378. Land Banking

**What it is:** Buying land in future growth corridors and holding until appreciation — near upcoming highways, metro lines, industrial zones, airports.

**Players:** Individual investors, HNIs, large developers buying land banks.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 (sell appreciated land) | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — 3-10 years.

**Challenges:** 💰 Capital locked for years with zero income · 📜 Title verification critical · 🌊 Policy/zoning changes can devalue land · 📈 Holding costs (property tax, security, legal).

**Mistake:** Buying without clear title. Land disputes in India take decades in courts. Triple-verify every document before buying.

**One-liner:** Buy land and wait — potentially massive returns, but title verification must be obsessive.

---

### 🟢 379. Rental Income Properties

**What it is:** Buying property and renting for monthly income — apartments, shops, offices, warehouses.

**Players:** Individual landlords (crores), Embassy REIT (institutional), Brookfield (big).

**Model:** Rental 🔑 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium — income from month one.

**Challenges:** 💰 High capital for purchase · ⚙ Tenant management · 📈 Rental yields in India low (2-3%) vs mutual funds · 📜 Rental agreements, police verification.

**Mistake:** Buying where you want to live, not where tenants want to live. ₹20L apartment near IT park at 7% yield beats ₹1Cr posh area at 2.4% yield.

**One-liner:** Buy and rent property — analyze rental yield, not just appreciation; yield matters more than address.

---

### 🟡 380. Fix & Flip (Renovation)

**What it is:** Buying undervalued/distressed properties, renovating them, and selling at profit.

**Players:** Individual real estate investors, property renovation contractors.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium — 3-6 months per flip.

**Challenges:** 💰 Purchase + renovation capital · 🧠 Must accurately estimate renovation costs · ⚙ Contractor management (delays, cost overruns) · 📈 Finding undervalued properties is the skill.

**Mistake:** Over-renovating for the neighborhood. A ₹10L kitchen in a middle-class colony doesn't increase property value by ₹10L. Renovate to neighborhood standards, not luxury standards.

**One-liner:** Buy cheap, renovate, sell — renovate to neighborhood standards, not your personal luxury taste.

---

### 🔴 381. REITs (Real Estate Investment Trusts)

**What it is:** Creating or investing in listed funds that own income-generating real estate — offices, malls, warehouses — distributing rental income to unit holders.

**Players:** Embassy Office Parks REIT (Indian, big), Mindspace REIT (Indian, big), Brookfield India REIT.

**Model:** Rental 🔑 (distributed as dividends) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 SEBI regulations for REIT listing · 💰 Minimum ₹500Cr portfolio to list · 🧠 Asset management expertise · 📈 Indian REIT market still developing.

**Mistake:** For investors: treating REITs like stocks (trading frequently). REITs are for rental income — hold long-term like property, not like day-trading stocks.

**One-liner:** Create/invest in REITs — fractional real estate ownership; for operators, need ₹500Cr+ portfolio to list.

---

### 🔴 382. Fractional Ownership Platforms

**What it is:** Building platforms where multiple investors jointly own commercial property — each buying a fraction (₹10L-25L) and earning proportional rent.

**Players:** Strata (Indian, big), hBits (Indian, medium), PropShare (Indian), individual fractional platforms.

**Model:** Commission 💰 (management fee + setup fee) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 SEBI now regulating fractional ownership (SM-REIT framework) · 💰 Platform + legal setup · 🧠 Asset selection and management · 📈 Building investor trust.

**Mistake:** Not registering under SEBI's SM-REIT framework. Unregistered platforms face regulatory action. Compliance is now mandatory.

**One-liner:** Build fractional ownership platforms — SEBI SM-REIT registration is now mandatory; don't operate unregistered.

---

### 🟡 383. Commercial Lease Investing

**What it is:** Buying commercial properties (offices, shops, warehouses) with existing tenants and long-term leases for stable rental income.

**Players:** Individual HNI investors, family offices, institutional investors.

**Model:** Rental 🔑 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium — 6-9% yields typical for commercial.

**Challenges:** 💰 Commercial properties cost ₹50L-50Cr+ · ⚙ Tenant vacating risk · 📈 Location determines demand · 📜 Lease agreement terms critical.

**Mistake:** Not verifying tenant quality. A property leased to a Fortune 500 company is worth more than one leased to a struggling startup. Tenant quality IS property quality.

**One-liner:** Invest in leased commercial property — tenant quality determines investment quality; Fortune 500 tenant > unknown startup.

---

### 🟡 384. Student Housing Investment

**What it is:** Developing or investing in purpose-built student accommodation near colleges and universities.

**Players:** Stanza Living (Indian, operator), Zolo (Indian), individual PG/hostel investors.

**Model:** Rental 🔑 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📈 Traditional PGs compete on price · ⚙ Student turnover every year · 💰 Must be near university campuses · 🌊 Vacation months have zero occupancy.

**Mistake:** Building far from campus. Students walk or cycle — anything more than 2 km from campus is a hard sell regardless of amenities.

**One-liner:** Build student housing — location within 2 km of campus is non-negotiable; everything else is secondary.

---

### 🔴 385. Senior Living Facilities

**What it is:** Developing retirement communities — independent living, assisted living, memory care — for elderly residents.

**Players:** Ashiana Housing (Indian, big), Columbia Pacific (Indian, big), individual senior living developers.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 (unit sale) + Subscription 🔄 (monthly maintenance + care) | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow.

**Challenges:** 💰 Medical and care infrastructure expensive · 🧠 Healthcare + real estate + hospitality combined expertise · 📈 Indian cultural preference to live with family (changing slowly) · 📜 No specific senior living regulation yet.

**Mistake:** Building senior homes without medical infrastructure. Residents need emergency medical response, pharmacy, physiotherapy, and caregiver access. Without healthcare, it's just a gated community, not senior living.

**One-liner:** Build senior living — medical infrastructure is the differentiator; without healthcare, it's just another housing project.

---

### 🟡 386. Storage Unit Facilities

**What it is:** Operating self-storage facilities — secure, rented storage units for individuals and businesses to store belongings.

**Players:** StoreMore (Indian, small), Spacioss (Indian, small), individual storage operators — early market.

**Model:** Rental 🔑 (monthly) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📈 Self-storage culture new in India · 💰 Real estate + security + fire safety investment · ⚙ Occupancy builds slowly · 📜 No specific self-storage regulations.

**Mistake:** Building in cheap, remote locations. Customers need convenient access — near residential areas or business districts. Remote locations get no customers.

**One-liner:** Operate self-storage — location near residential areas is critical; remote warehouses don't attract self-storage customers.

---

### 🟡 387. Parking Lot & Garage Investment

**What it is:** Owning or operating paid parking facilities — surface lots, multi-level parking, automated parking systems in urban areas.

**Players:** Park+ (Indian, medium — tech), Get My Parking (Indian, medium), individual parking operators, municipal parking.

**Model:** Rental 🔑 (hourly/monthly) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 💰 Multi-level parking ₹5Cr-50Cr · 📜 Municipal tenders for public parking · 📈 Free parking expectations in India · ⚙ Automated systems need maintenance.

**Mistake:** Not adding technology. Digital payment, app-based booking, and automated entry/exit increase throughput and revenue per spot by 20-40%.

**One-liner:** Invest in parking — add digital payment and app booking to maximize revenue per spot.

