# Sector 11: Healthcare & Wellness

```
⏱  TIMELINE:       1 – 7 years
💰 STARTING COST:  ₹2L – ₹100Cr+
🔄 REVENUE SPEED:  Medium
DEPENDS ON:        Licenses, qualified staff, equipment, trust
```

---

## 11.1 Healthcare Delivery

---

### 🔴 388. Clinic / Hospital

**What it is:** Operating a healthcare facility — single-specialty clinic, multi-specialty hospital, or super-specialty hospital.

**Players:** Apollo Hospitals (big), Fortis (big), Max Healthcare (big), Narayana Health (big — affordable), individual clinics (lakhs).

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 + Product Sale 📦 (pharmacy) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 💰 Hospital ₹10Cr-1,000Cr+ · 📜 Clinical Establishment Act license · 🧠 Qualified doctors, nurses, technicians · ⚙ 24/7 operations · 📈 Insurance reimbursement complexities.

**Mistake:** Building a hospital without a star doctor. Patients choose hospitals based on the doctor, not the building. Recruit top specialists before opening.

**One-liner:** Run a hospital — recruit star doctors first; patients follow doctors, not buildings.

---

### 🟡 389. Diagnostic Lab & Imaging Center

**What it is:** Running pathology labs (blood tests, urine, biopsy) and imaging centers (X-ray, MRI, CT scan, ultrasound).

**Players:** Dr. Lal PathLabs (big), SRL Diagnostics (big), Thyrocare (big), individual diagnostic labs.

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 + Franchise 🏪 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 NABL accreditation highly recommended · 💰 MRI/CT equipment ₹1Cr-10Cr · 🧠 Qualified pathologists and radiologists · 📈 Price war driven by online booking platforms · ⚙ Report accuracy is critical.

**Mistake:** Competing on price for basic blood tests. Differentiate with accuracy, turnaround time, and home collection service. One wrong report destroys a lab's reputation.

**One-liner:** Run diagnostic labs — accuracy and turnaround time differentiate more than price; one wrong report is fatal to reputation.

---

### 🟡 390. Pharmacy & Drug Store

**What it is:** Retail pharmacy selling prescription medicines, OTC drugs, supplements, personal care, medical devices.

**Players:** Apollo Pharmacy (big), MedPlus (big), Netmeds (online, big), individual pharmacies (8L+ in India).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 + Franchise 🏪 | **Revenue:** ⚡ Fast.

**Challenges:** 📜 Drug license mandatory · 📈 Online pharmacies (PharmEasy, 1mg) cutting prices · 💰 Inventory of 5,000+ SKUs · ⚙ Expiry management · 🧠 Must have qualified pharmacist.

**Mistake:** Opening far from hospitals. Pharmacies depend on prescription walk-ins from nearby doctors/hospitals. Best location = adjacent to a busy hospital.

**One-liner:** Sell medicines — locate next to hospitals; prescription walk-in traffic is your lifeline.

---

### 🟡 391. Dental Clinic

**What it is:** Providing dental services — check-ups, fillings, root canals, braces, implants, cosmetic dentistry.

**Players:** Clove Dental (Indian, big chain), Sabka Dentist (Indian, big), individual dental clinics.

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

