## 12.1 Banking & Lending

---

### 🔴 418. Small Finance Bank

**What it is:** Operating a bank focused on financial inclusion — serving underbanked sections, small businesses, micro-loans, savings accounts.

**Players:** AU Small Finance Bank (big), Equitas (big), Ujjivan (big), Jana (big).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 (interest income) | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — 3-5 years to profitability.

**Challenges:** 📜 RBI license — extremely difficult to obtain · 💰 ₹200Cr+ minimum capital · 🧠 Banking operations expertise · ⚙ Branch network and technology · 📜 CRR, SLR, priority sector lending norms.

**Mistake:** This is not an entrepreneurial play — it requires RBI license that is nearly impossible for new entrants. Consider NBFC route instead.

**One-liner:** Operate a small finance bank — RBI license is nearly impossible for new entrants; NBFC is the realistic route.

---

### 🔴 419. NBFC (Non-Banking Finance Company)

**What it is:** A financial company that lends money but isn't a bank — doesn't accept demand deposits. Personal loans, business loans, vehicle finance, gold loans.

**Players:** Bajaj Finance (big), Muthoot (big), Manappuram (big), individual NBFCs (thousands).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 (interest income — spread between borrowing cost and lending rate) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 RBI NBFC registration (₹2Cr+ net owned funds) · 💰 Capital intensive — need money to lend money · 🌊 NPA (bad loan) risk · 📜 Increasing RBI scrutiny · ⚙ Collections management.

**Mistake:** Lending without robust credit assessment. Easy money out = hard money back. The core skill is saying NO to bad borrowers.

**One-liner:** Run an NBFC — the skill is in who you DON'T lend to; bad loan assessment destroys NBFCs.

---

### 🔴 420. Microfinance Institution

**What it is:** Providing small loans (₹5,000-₹1,00,000) to low-income borrowers — women's self-help groups, micro-entrepreneurs, rural poor.

**Players:** Bandhan (started as MFI, now bank), CreditAccess Grameen (big), Arohan (big), individual MFIs.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 (interest income) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 RBI MFI regulations, interest rate caps · 🌊 Loan waivers by state governments destroy repayment culture · ⚙ Field staff in remote areas · 💰 Capital needs · 👥 Political interference.

**Mistake:** Over-lending in one geography. When a drought/flood hits, your entire portfolio defaults. Geographic diversification is survival.

**One-liner:** Provide microloans — diversify geographically; concentrated lending in one area = concentrated risk.

