### 🔴 421. Peer-to-Peer Lending Platform

**What it is:** Building a platform connecting individual lenders with borrowers — enabling P2P lending without a bank intermediary.

**Players:** Faircent (Indian, big), LenDenClub (Indian, big), Liquiloans (Indian), 12% Club (BharatPe).

**Model:** Commission 💰 (platform fee from both parties) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 RBI NBFC-P2P license mandatory · 💰 ₹2Cr+ net owned funds · 📈 Building two-sided marketplace (lenders + borrowers) · 🌊 Default risk affects lender trust · ⚙ Collections on defaulted loans.

**Mistake:** Not maintaining sufficient risk reserves. When defaults spike, lender trust evaporates. Maintain a contingency fund to absorb some losses.

**One-liner:** Build P2P lending — lender trust depends on managing defaults; maintain risk reserves.

