### 🔴 466. Water Taxi / Ferry Service

**What it is:** Operating passenger boats and ferries — river crossings, coastal routes, backwater tourism, urban water transit.

**Players:** Kerala SWTD (govt), Mumbai Water Transport (emerging), individual ferry operators.

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 (per passenger) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 Maritime Board/IWT (Inland Water Transport) licenses · 💰 Vessel costs ₹50L-5Cr · ⚙ Weather dependency · 📜 Safety regulations (life jackets, capacity limits) · 📈 Limited routes in India.

**Mistake:** Operating without proper safety equipment. One accident without safety compliance = criminal charges + service shut down + loss of life.

**One-liner:** Operate water transport — safety compliance is absolute; one accident without life jackets is criminal.

