## 13.3 Supply Chain & Tech

---

### 🟡 468. Inventory Management System

**What it is:** Software for tracking inventory — stock levels, reordering, warehouse locations, expiry dates, multi-channel sync.

**Players:** Zoho Inventory (Indian, big), Unicommerce (Indian, big), individual inventory software startups.

**Model:** Subscription 🔄 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📈 Zoho and free tools competing · ⚙ Must integrate with marketplaces (Amazon, Flipkart), accounting (Tally), and shipping · 🧠 Understanding inventory management practices.

**Mistake:** Building standalone inventory software. Must integrate with Amazon, Flipkart, Shopify, Tally, and shipping partners. Integration is the value, not just counting stock.

**One-liner:** Build inventory software — integration with marketplaces and accounting is the value; standalone counting is worthless.

---

### 🟡 469. Route Optimization Software

**What it is:** Software that optimizes delivery routes — minimizing fuel, time, and distance for fleets delivering across multiple stops.

**Players:** FarEye (Indian, big), Locus (Indian, big), individual logistics tech startups.

**Model:** Subscription 🔄 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 🧠 Algorithm optimization expertise · 📈 Google Maps API provides basic routing · ⚙ Indian addresses are imprecise (no standard format) · 💰 Enterprise sales cycles.

**Mistake:** Using Western address systems for India. Indian addresses are chaotic — "near SBI bank, opposite temple, 3rd floor." Your algorithm must handle imprecise, landmark-based addresses.

**One-liner:** Build route optimization — must handle India's imprecise, landmark-based addressing; Western address logic fails here.

---

### 🟡 470. Fleet Tracking & Telematics

**What it is:** GPS tracking + vehicle diagnostics — real-time location, speed monitoring, fuel tracking, driver behavior, maintenance alerts.

**Players:** Fleetx (Indian, medium), LocoNav (Indian, medium), MapmyIndia (Indian, big — maps + fleet), individual GPS providers.

**Model:** Subscription 🔄 (per-vehicle monthly) + Product Sale 📦 (device) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📈 Cheap Chinese GPS devices flooding market · 🧠 Telematics data analysis · ⚙ Cellular connectivity in remote areas · 💰 Scaling device deployment.

**Mistake:** Selling just GPS location. The value is in analytics — fuel theft detection, driver scorecards, predictive maintenance alerts. Raw location data is commodity.

**One-liner:** Track fleets — analytics (fuel theft, driver scores, maintenance) is the premium; raw GPS location is commodity.

---

### 🔴 471. Drone Delivery Service

**What it is:** Using drones for last-mile delivery — medicines, food, e-commerce parcels, emergency supplies to remote areas.

**Players:** Zomato (testing drone delivery), Dunzo (testing), TechEagle (Indian, small), Redwing Labs (Indian, small — medical delivery).

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — regulations still evolving.

**Challenges:** 📜 DGCA regulations — BVLOS (Beyond Visual Line of Sight) approvals limited · 🧠 Autonomous flight software · 💰 Drone fleet costs · 📈 Very early stage in India.

**Mistake:** Building for urban delivery where ground delivery is fine. Drones make most sense for remote/hard-to-reach areas — hilly terrain, islands, emergency medical supply.

**One-liner:** Deliver via drones — most viable for remote/emergency use cases where ground delivery fails, not urban convenience.

