### 🔴 472. Autonomous Vehicle Tech

**What it is:** Developing self-driving technology — sensors, LIDAR, computer vision, path planning for autonomous trucks, buses, or cars.

**Players:** Waymo (big, global), Tesla (big), Ati Motors (Indian, small — autonomous industrial vehicles), Flux Auto (Indian, small).

**Model:** Licensing 📜 + Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — 5-10 years.

**Challenges:** 🧠 AI + robotics + automotive engineering · 💰 Massive R&D costs · 📜 No autonomous driving regulations in India yet · 📈 Indian road conditions (chaotic) are world's hardest for autonomous driving · ⚙ Safety validation.

**Mistake:** Targeting passenger cars in India first. Indian traffic is the hardest for autonomy. Start with controlled environments — warehouse robots, mining vehicles, airport tugs.

**One-liner:** Build self-driving tech — start with controlled environments (warehouses, mines); Indian public roads are the world's hardest autonomous driving challenge.

