### 🟡 473. Supply Chain Consulting

**What it is:** Advising companies on supply chain optimization — procurement, inventory, logistics, demand planning, network design.

**Players:** McKinsey (big), Kearney (big), individual supply chain consultants.

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 🧠 Deep supply chain + analytical expertise · 📈 In-house supply chain teams at large companies · 💰 Feast-or-famine project flow.

**Mistake:** Giving theoretical advice. Companies want specific savings — "we'll reduce your inventory carrying cost by ₹2Cr" not "optimize your supply chain."

**One-liner:** Consult on supply chains — quantify specific savings in rupees; abstract "optimization" doesn't get contracts.

