### 🟡 475. Reverse Logistics (Returns)

**What it is:** Managing product returns — pickup, inspection, refurbishment, restocking, disposal. Critical for e-commerce where return rates are 15-30%.

**Players:** Reverse Logistics Company (Indian, medium), Delhivery (returns division), individual returns management companies.

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 (per-return) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** ⚙ Returns are unpredictable in volume and timing · 🧠 Must grade returned items (resellable, refurbishable, scrap) · 📈 E-commerce returns growing = opportunity · 💰 Processing returns is labor-intensive.

**Mistake:** Treating all returns the same. The value is in grading — A-grade returns can be resold at 80-90% price, B-grade refurbished, C-grade scrapped. Grading accuracy = revenue recovery.

**One-liner:** Manage e-commerce returns — grading accuracy (resellable vs refurbish vs scrap) directly determines revenue recovery.

