### 🔴 476. Port & Terminal Operations

**What it is:** Operating port terminals — container handling, bulk cargo, liquid terminals. Loading/unloading ships, storage, transport.

**Players:** Adani Ports (big), DP World (big, global), JNPT (govt), APM Terminals (big).

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 (per-container/per-ton charges) | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow — PPP concessions run 30+ years.

**Challenges:** 💰 ₹500Cr-10,000Cr+ investment · 📜 Government concession/BOT agreements · ⚙ Massive crane and equipment infrastructure · 👥 Strategic asset — government oversight · 🕐 30-year concession horizons.

**Mistake:** This is exclusively for large conglomerates (Adani, DP World scale). Small players can enter through ICD (Inland Container Depot) operations with much lower investment.

**One-liner:** Operate ports — conglomerate territory; smaller players enter through ICD (Inland Container Depot) operations.

